undertake /ˌʌndəˈteɪk/

(undertaking,undertook,undertaken,undertakes) 

1. V-T When you undertake a task or job, you start doing it and accept responsibility for it. 从事; 承担 

例： She undertook the task of monitoring the elections. 她承担了监督选举的任务。 

2. V-T If you undertake to do something, you promise that you will do it. 承诺 

例： He undertook to edit the text himself. 他承诺亲自编辑正文。

